{"analytics_identifier":null,"base_path":"/government/organisations/gov-facility-services-limited/about","content_id":"6faa7f66-b46d-403c-8109-a2fc93e0816e","description":"Gov Facility Services Limited (GFSL) provides facility maintenance services to prisons across the South of England.","details":{"attachments":[],"body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><h2 id=\"responsibilities\">Responsibilities</h2>\n\n<p>Delivering our services in Prisons is challenging, but rewarding. Our teams enable a key part of the Justice system to work: allowing people to be housed securely and safely while in prison.</p>\n\n<p>We also help the Prison Service reduce reoffending by providing opportunities for prisoners to develop skills and gain work experience. We currently support over a million hours per year of work by prisoners across the 49 prisons we maintain.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"who-we-are\">Who we are</h2>\n\n<p>We are a not-for-profit company working closely with HM Prison and Probation Service (HMPPS), to deliver a range of facility services, including statutory and mandatory planned maintenance, reactive repair, cleaning, stores operation and Project works.</p>\n\n<p>Gov Facility Services Limited is a company registered at Companies House, with the registration number: 11061429</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"objectives\">Objectives</h2>\n\n<p>Our core objective is to support HMPPS in providing a safe working environment and maintaining and improving the physical infrastructure of their prisons. We only work in prisons run by HMPPS.</p>\n\n<p>Our core focus centres around four  areas:</p>\n\n<p>Safety - our focus is to keep everyone safe. We work to establish an environment with strong moral responsibilities and control for Health &amp; Safety and Technical Compliance.</p>\n\n<p>Reliability - we want to be recognised for delivering a reliable and trusted service with a strong performance-based culture. We will be open and honest with our customers.</p>\n\n<p>Efficiency - we aim to deliver services in the most cost-effective manner in order to maximise the value from our allocated budgets.</p>\n\n<p>Our People - we recognise our people are key to success. We will develop and offer them opportunities to achieve their personal potential.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"where-we-work\">Where we work</h2>\n\n<p>GFSL Works Departments deliver the Facilities Maintenance (FM) service at 49 prisons across the South of England on behalf of HMPPS.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"greater-london-and-surrounds\">Greater London and surrounds:</h3>\n\n<p>HMYOI Aylesbury, HMP &amp; HMYOI Bullingdon, HMP Coldingley, HMP Downview, Feltham YOI, HMP Grendon, HMP Highdown, HMP Huntercombe, HMP Pentonville, HMP Send, HMP Springhill,  HMP Wandsworth, HMP Wormwood Scrubs.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"east-of-england\">East of England:</h3>\n\n<p>HMP Bedford, HMP Bure, HMP Chelmsford, HMP Highpoint, HMP Hollesley Bay, HMP Little Hey,  HMP The Mount, HMP Norwich, HMP Warren Hill, HMP Wayland, HMP Whitemoor, HMP Woodhill.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"kent-and-sussex\">Kent and Sussex:</h3>\n\n<p>HMP Belmarsh, HMP Blantyre House, HMP Cookham Wood, HMP East Sutton Park, HMP Elmley, HMP Ford, HMP Lewes, HMP Maidstone, HMP Rochester, HMP Standford Hill, HMP Swaleside.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"south-west-england\">South West England:</h3>\n\n<p>HMP Albany, HMP Bristol, HMP Channings Wood, HMP Dartmoor, HMP Eastwood Park, HMP Erlestoke, HMP Exeter, HMP Guys Marsh, HMP Leyhill, HMP Parkhurst, HMP Portland, HMP The Verne, HMP Winchester.</p>\n</div>","change_history":[{"note":"First published.","public_timestamp":"2020-05-22T08:48:45Z"}],"corporate_information_groups":[{"contents":["fb49ed5f-e0d6-4946-9601-62a8e8df6211","489a3667-ff8e-4f97-bf3e-28e46e21a5a6"],"name":"Access our information"},{"contents":["859c9545-dfbe-4978-8f8b-6e881edb9254","8419fd32-7134-4874-a7de-0e81d60cf554",{"title":"Jobs","url":"https://findajob.dwp.gov.uk/search?q=Gov+Facility+Services"}],"name":"Jobs and contracts"}],"headers":[{"id":"responsibilities","level":2,"text":"Responsibilities"},